messages.content:
Marketing have fucked up. I need you all to check your quotes for products in the below list - ONLY TO Wholesale customers. For an unknown reason that I have folded about, they've price-matched our new real mounts buy price to the wholesale sell on the top 40 lines. So anything on that list we've sold to a wholesale customer in the last 10 days hasn't turned a profit.

If you've got current quotes on the go for these SKU's, created post Jan FEB 27, they'll have the same issue, and you need to jump on them to amend quotes and inform customers.

Apologies for the fuck around.

1. RAM-B-101U
2. RAM-B-202U
3. RAM-B-101U-C
4. RAM-B-201U-C
5. RAM-B-201U
6. RAM-B-238U
7. RAM-B-224-1U
8. RAM-HOL-UN7BU
9. RAM-B-101U-A
10. RAM-HOL-UN11U
11. RAM-202U
12. RAM-HOL-UN10BU
13. RAP-B-201U
14. RAM-316-HDR-202U
15. RAM-B-166-UN7U
16. RAM-HOL-UN9U
17. RAM-B-230U
18. RAM-B-201U-A
19. RAM-B-316-1-202U
20. RAP-B-224-1U
21. RAP-B-201-A
22. RAP-B-400U
23. RAM-HOL-SAM7PU
24. RAM-201U
25. RAP-SB-224-2-UN7U
26. RAM-B-166-202U

Additionally, here are the orders that were entered via API or B2B portal during that period. If some accounts order regularly, just drop them a message and say, "Hey, we made an errorr and you're the beneficiary. Items will be more expensive in the future but still competitive". Obviously you don't want to inform them they bought at our cost price, just say there was an error. SEVA, TAXI COMMS and a few others will definitely purchase again and may ask why the price changed. Thanks, Connect with Me on LinkedIn

Hi team,

emails.subject: FW: Urgent - Dell Server Issue
emails.body:
Hi Team,

Following up on the Dell server issue reported earlier today. The server is still offline and impacting critical services. Please prioritize resolving this immediately.

Regards,
Bianca

emails.subject: Re: FW: Urgent - Dell Server Issue
emails.body:
Hi Bianca,

I'm currently investigating the issue. Initial diagnostics point to a potential hardware failure with the RAID controller. I'm working on isolating the problem and will provide an update within the hour.

Thanks,
David

emails.subject: Dell Server Status Update
emails.body:
Hi Bianca and David,

David, I've checked the server logs and found error messages related to disk I/O. This seems to confirm the RAID controller issue. I'm available to assist if needed.

Thanks,
Sarah

emails.subject: Re: Dell Server Status Update
emails.body:
Hi Sarah,

Thanks for the additional information. I'm attempting to replace the RAID controller now. It's a delicate process, but I'm proceeding cautiously.

Regards,
David

emails.subject: Dell Server Back Online

emails.subject: Re: HCLTech - RAM Mount quote
emails.body: Sorry for the delay, please see attached quote.

Hi Parker,

Thanks for your assistance with this quote.

Do you know what the warranty procedure for RAM parts are? According to their website, there is a lifetime warranty, however the warranty claiming appears to be formatted only for US customers. Would we go through you for warranty claims?

Regards,

*Joshua Shields*
Account Manager
Apple DEP ID – 6280D50

*View our 2024 Catalogue Here!*

Hi Josh,

RAM mounts do have a lifetime warranty but that does not cover electronic components, they range from 1-3 years. We would just need to receive an image of the faulty product and the order it was from. How many cradles is this customer looking at? We have alternative cradle solutions for the Tab Active 4 pro which are compatible with RAM mounts.

Tim Lynch
Strike Group Australia
Corporate Sales Director
1/263 Toombul Rd, Northgate, QLD 4013
*M* + 61 417 703 695
*E* tl@strike.com.au
*P* 1300 792 044

I have attached some pictures for you to better understand the topic. I hope this helps to get a good rebate on your pricing.

Best,

Oliver
